                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>1816 De Lancey Place.<lb/>
                Friday March 18th 1892.<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear Mr Morais&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>Your kind note&#44; was the<lb/> first intimation&#44; we had<lb/> that sickness &#38; death had<lb/> visited your family.<lb/>  The loss of a child is<lb/> always felt&#45;&#45;especially&#44; by<lb/> its <hi rend="underline">mother</hi>&#44; and I <hi rend="underline">do feel</hi><lb/> for your daughter Rebecca<lb/> for&#44; <hi rend="underline">I know</hi> the sorrow &#38; grief<lb/> felt for the loss of an infant<lb/> God took two&#44; out of my<lb/> flock&#45;&#45;&#38; I have never ceased<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>to grieve for them&#44; or to<lb/> remember&#33;&#33; but <hi rend="underline">you</hi> have<lb/> a great example before you<lb/> for&#44; when Solomons son was<lb/> ill&#44; he prayed &#38; fasted&#44; but<lb/> when they told him&#44; the child<lb/> was &#34;dead&#44;&#34; he rose up &#38; did<lb/> eat &#38; left off praying&#44; for he<lb/> said I shall go to him&#44; but<lb/> he will not return to me.<lb/></p>
            <p>The weather has been so<lb/> wintry &#38; inclement that none<lb/> of my daughters could go to<lb/> express sympathy with your<lb/> daughters&#44; but they all feel<lb/> it&#44; as well as myself.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>And&#44; now let me congratulate<lb/> you&#44; my dear Mr Morais<lb/> upon having attained the<lb/> 41st year of your ministry<lb/> in <hi rend="underline">our</hi> congregation&#33; and<lb/> you may well say&#44; with Samuel<lb/> &#34;whose oz&#44; have I taken&#33; or whose<lb/> ass have I taken&#33; or whom<lb/> have I defrauded&#44; or of whose<lb/> hand have I received any bribe<lb/> and&#44; I will return it to you.&#34;<lb/></p>
            <p>But&#44; <hi rend="underline">you</hi> can lay your<lb/> hand upon your heart&#44; I<lb/> like Samuel&#44; feel the power<lb/> of a <hi rend="underline">clear conscience within</hi><lb/> Yours ever respectfully<lb/> Sara Mordecai<lb/></p>
            </body>
